                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature steps onto the trap's pressure plate (indicated on the map);</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The front of the iron maiden slams shut with incredible force and locks itself. The triggering creature takes [[/r 4d10+10 #piercing]] piercing damage and [[/r 2d6 #persistent bleed]] @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Persistent Damage]{Persistent Bleed Damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"26\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Slam Shut DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save; if the creature critically succeeds, they avoid the trap completely). The triggering creature is also immobilized. The victim can end their immobilization only once a creature outside the iron maiden unlocks the device (requiring two successful <span data-pf2-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-dc=\"28\" data-pf2-traits=\"manipulate,action:disable-a-device\" data-pf2-label=\"Unlock Iron Maiden DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> checks to Disable a Device) or breaks the iron maiden, after which the trapped creature must succeed at a DC 25 check to Escape the trap's spike-lined interior.</p>"
